text: E. australis may refer to: * Elsinoë australis, a plant pathogen species that causes sweet orange scab * Emex australis, a synonym of Rumex hypogaeus, the doublegee or three-cornered jack, a herbaceous plant species found in South Africa and Australia * Eubalaena australis, the Southern right whale, a baleen whale species ==See also== * Australis (disambiguation)
title: E. australis
